sec.p:
From above equations the $\mathrm{A}, \mathrm{B}, \mathrm{C}, \mathrm{D}$ matrices for transfer function are as follows
\begin{equation*}
A =
\begin{bmatrix}
0 & 0 & -(1 - d)/L_1 & (1 - d)/L_1 \\
0 & 0 & 0 & -1/L_2 \\
(1 - d)/C_H & 0 & (-1)/(R_H \ast C_H) & 0 \\
-(1 - d)/C & (1)/C & 0 & 0
\end{bmatrix}
\end{equation*}
\begin{equation*}
B =
\begin{bmatrix}
1/L_1 \\
0 \\
0 \\
0
\end{bmatrix}, \quad
C =
\begin{bmatrix}
0 & 0 & 1 & 0
\end{bmatrix}, \quad
D =
\begin{bmatrix}
0 & 0 & 0 & 0
\end{bmatrix}
\end{equation*}

Similarly for buck mode A, B, C, D matrices for transfer function are as follows.
\begin{equation*}
A =
\begin{bmatrix}
0 & 0 & 1/L_1 & (1 - D)/L_1 \\
0 & 0 & 0 & 1/L_2 \\
(2d - 1)/C_2 & 0 & (1 - 2d)/C_2R & 0 \\
(1 - d)/C & -1/C & 0 & 0
\end{bmatrix}
\end{equation*}
\begin{equation*}
\mathrm{B}=\begin{bmatrix}-(1-\mathrm{d}) / \mathrm{L} 1 \\ -(1-\mathrm{d}) / \mathrm{L} 2 \\ 0 \\ 0\end{bmatrix}
\end{equation*}
\begin{equation*}
\mathrm{C}=\left[\begin{array}{llll}0 & 0 & 1 & 0\end{array}\right]
\end{equation*}
\begin{equation*}
\mathrm{D}=\left[\begin{array}{llll}0 & 0 & 0 & 0\end{array}\right]
\end{equation*}

